[@JsonDeserialize][1] should help you with this you can write your custom deserializer class which can do validation on data like so:

    import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonParser;
    import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;
    import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationContext;
    import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.StdDeserializer;
    
    import java.io.IOException;
    
    public class DataHandler extends StdDeserializer&lt;Object&gt; {
        protected DataHandler(Class&lt;?&gt; vc) {
            super(vc);
        }
    
        public Object deserialize(JsonParser jsonParser, DeserializationContext deserializationContext) throws IOException, JsonProcessingException {
            String str = jsonParser.getText();
            String validatedStr = validateStr(str);
            return str;
        }
    
        private String validateStr(String str) {
            // write validation code here. Handle illegal quoted characters, add try/catch, etc
            return str;
        }
    }

Once you have that you can simply annotate `private Object data;` with your `DataHandler` like so:

    import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonIgnoreProperties;
    import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonInclude;
    import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.annotation.JsonDeserialize;
    
    @JsonInclude(JsonInclude.Include.NON_NULL)
    @JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)
    public class EventData extends BasicDBObject{
        /**
         * Social information of user
         */
        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;
    
        @JsonDeserialize(using = DataHandler.class)
        private Object data;
    
        public Object getData() {
            return data;
        }
    
        public void setData(Object data) {
            this.data = data;
        }
    } 

Notice the `@JsonDeserialize` annotation on the `data` above. Good article to read on this with a working example is [here][2]


